🧑🏻‍🍳 cooking w cassian episode: banana & veggie muffins. 

these are packed w tons of protein & fiber. super moist, flavorful and delicious. even i crave them! i also love that cassian knows exactly what type of veggies going into the muffin. even though he doesn't eat zucchini by itself i'm glad he loves to cook w it and eat it in different ways! 

+ 3 cups of oatmeal 
+ 1/2 cup of cottage cheese 
+ 2 mashed bananas
+ 1/2 cup grated zucchini 
+ handful of grated carrots 
+ 1/4 cup nut butter 
+ 1/4 cup milk
+ 1 scoop of protein powder 
+ 1 tbsp baking powder
+ 1 tsp cinnamon 
+ 1 tbsp vanilla extract 
+ 2 tbsp of hemp seeds 
+ 2 tbsp of flax seeds 

mix everything & bake at 350 for 20 minutes or so

optional: 
+ 1/4 cup maple syrup (if you want them lightly sweet otherwise these aren't very sweet at all)
+ chocolate chips (we like the no sugar added ones from costco)
+ sprinkles cus they are fun!

here's something i read a long time ago that stuck w me when it comes to splurging responsibly:

+ if planning to splurge, it should be on pieces that will be an investment aka can be worn for my many years, classic, high quality, practical, useful; basically thinking about cost per wear. 
+ you could also splurge on rare items that you randomly or luckily came across aka things that have high value, resale-able, crazy sale items, profitable, something you can look back on years later and say "wow that was such a great purchase". 
+ and lastly, while it shouldn't done as often but splurge on items that just bring you pure joy, excitement, experience or happiness.

how i wash my cashmere, wool and delicates at home with @thelaundress - no dry cleaning necessary 🫧🧺

 #TLPartner i have been using The Laundress for years - it’s a staple in my laundry room. i’m so happy that they are back with their new formulas, and honestly nothing compares when it comes cleaning and maintaining my favorite pieces plus the scents are amazing.
 
here's my tips:
+cashmere & wool pieces go in a mesh bag to avoid snags
+ wash them in separate loads. first load is your delicates like silks, vintage pieces, lingerie, undergarments & the second load is your cashmere & wool pieces only. 
+ wash on the delicate cycle
+ after washing, lay them flat to dry so they keep their shape (very important do not put in your dryer, it can shrink and damage the fabric)

happy washing!
